            <div type="edition" xml:space="preserve"><head>Text</head><ab><lb n="1"/>
                <expan><abbr>L</abbr><ex>ucius</ex></expan> Caidius <lb n="2"/><expan><abbr>L</abbr><ex>uci</ex></expan> <supplied reason="lost"><expan><abbr>f</abbr><ex>ilius</ex></expan></supplied> <expan><abbr>Ser</abbr><ex>gia</ex></expan> Speratus <lb n="3"/>viv<expan><ex>u</ex><abbr>s</abbr></expan> sibi et Alfia<supplied reason="lost">e</supplied> <lb n="4"/><expan><abbr>Q</abbr><ex>uinti</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>f</abbr><ex>iliae</ex></expan> Secundae <lb n="5"/>uxori <lb n="6"/><expan><abbr>L</abbr><ex>ucio</ex></expan> Caidio <expan><abbr>L</abbr><ex>uci</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>f</abbr><ex>ilio</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>Ser</abbr><ex>gia</ex></expan> Afro <lb n="7"/>IIIIviro aedili <expan><abbr>f</abbr><ex>ilio</ex></expan>
            </ab></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Tiefe wegen Vermauerung unbekannt. Weiterer Beleg für nomen gentile Caidius: CIL IX 3088 = ILS 6531; vgl. AE 1982, 233. Vielleicht sind die beiden Personen verwandt. (A): Stein nicht verschollen. (B): Z. 1: Gaidius T(iti) f(ilius) statt Caidius L(uci) [f(ilius)]; Z. 3: viv(us) statt viv(u)s; Alfiae statt Alfia[e]; Z. 6: Gaidio statt Caidio; Z. 7: IIIviro statt IIIIviro.</p>
            </div>
